To Alex: Thank you.

To Jesse: Well, the only thing that's publically available right now is http://dict.collapsar.net/, where you can find:

* Kdict -- My wife's trilingual EN/JA/ZH concordance sort of thing. I do the software, she does the data (both halves are under active development so please forgive shortcomings)
* Wroget -- My implementation of an elecronic thesaurus, in the mode of a proper Roget's (not alphabetical).
* Wdict -- Just another webby dict server interface.

I'm currently working on a markup language and parser named Mint, which I hope won't suck (it's aiming to be somewhere between Textile and TeX on the "power", "flexibility", and "complexity" scales), and a unified home media cataloguing and access doohickey (and I mean all media -- digital and analogue texts, audio, and video) with no official name or even a good description yet. There's more down the road, but they're even more vague (one is best described as a "library metaserver"), and I don't like to traffic in vaporware --ShawnBoyette


